<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - AERODYNAMIC PANELS - ROOF AIR DEFLECTOR - INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Tighten all nuts until snug. After the air deflector is completely installed, tighten all
                    nuts/bolts to 31 ft-lbs. (42 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach rear supports and front mounting supports to cab roof.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach front mounting brackets to front mounting supports.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach stabilizer angle and bracket assembly to rear supports and front mounting brackets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach support tube to stabilizer angle brackets. Rear mounting support has to be attached
                to support tube prior to installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position air deflector and attach to front mounting brackets, stabilizer angles, and rear
                mounting supports.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
